<div id='communityQuestionsWithAnswers'>
<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/163758-my-heart-was-set-on-believing-his-stories">My heart was set on believing his stories. I am from Kazakhstan, and I am ethnically half Kazakh and lived in the country during Soviet times. All of the story of Mikhail can not be true, not even close. It shows the authors personal agenda to describe/criticize what he does not know, never experienced himself and failed to get the facts. Whether he is positive or negative, it screams lack of facts, ideas, knowledge.</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_163758'><a id="like_count_community_question_163758" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/163758?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">13 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F1427.The_Zahir">like</a></span>

