        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer9547015" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer618006023132494151">I was diasspointed with this and I would consider myself a fan of Paolo Coelho. I just don&apos;t think this lived up to his usual work. The plot was weak and there was a lot of annoying, sentimental stream-of-consciousness drivel about the meaning of love and the meaning of life. It&apos;s true that these are Coelho&apos;s usual themes but I think he&apos;s gotten a bit carried away with all the sentiment in this novel and forgotten the story in the process. The only thing that kept me reading until the end was my</span>
  <span id="freeText618006023132494151" style="display:none">I was diasspointed with this and I would consider myself a fan of Paolo Coelho. I just don't think this lived up to his usual work. The plot was weak and there was a lot of annoying, sentimental stream-of-consciousness drivel about the meaning of love and the meaning of life. It's true that these are Coelho's usual themes but I think he's gotten a bit carried away with all the sentiment in this novel and forgotten the story in the process. The only thing that kept me reading until the end was my enduring hate of the main character....he's one of those 'love to hate him' characters.</span>
  <a data-text-id="618006023132494151" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

