    <div class="elementListBrownSeparator"></div>



  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2376178259" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2376178259" />
    <a title="Marziye Foroughi" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/51177450-marziye-foroughi"><img alt="Marziye Foroughi" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1603991215p2/51177450.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2376178259?book_show_action=true">May 11, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Marziye Foroughi" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Marziye Foroughi" href="/user/show/51177450-marziye-foroughi">Marziye Foroughi</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2376178259" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3073967418664227463">I believe The Zahir is a chain of events with really great quotations rather than a novel because it has no climax, rising and falling action. It deals with Sufism, psychology and somehow magic realism. Its main themes are love, loss, obsession, marriage.<br/>Coelho&apos;s words resonated deeply within me and in fact, helped me to &quot;see&quot; and unlock some feelings that I haven&apos;t been able to understand for quite some time. <br/>you should know yourself before doing anything special in your life. this is the rule </span>
  <span id="freeText3073967418664227463" style="display:none">I believe The Zahir is a chain of events with really great quotations rather than a novel because it has no climax, rising and falling action. It deals with Sufism, psychology and somehow magic realism. Its main themes are love, loss, obsession, marriage.<br />Coelho's words resonated deeply within me and in fact, helped me to "see" and unlock some feelings that I haven't been able to understand for quite some time. <br />you should know yourself before doing anything special in your life. this is the rule I deeply believe in it after reading the Zahir.<br />I don't recommend this book to anyone who believes in traditional concepts of marriage.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3073967418664227463" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


